  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Junior Contract & Claims Management Professional",
  "description": "<p><strong>Role Purpose</strong></p><ul><li>Support project teams in administering contracts and managing commercial/claims activities across multidisciplinary, multinational project environments. </li><li>The role suits an early-career professional who learns quickly, follows structured guidance, and collaborates effectively across diverse teams and disciplines.</li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Track and maintain contract registers, obligations, deliverables, and milestones; ensure timely notifications.</li><li>Assist in drafting contractual correspondence with clear, concise English.</li><li>Liaise across Engineering, Procurement, Project Controls, and Site teams to consolidate inputs.</li><li>Gather facts and documents to analyze contractual and commercial claims.</li><li>Support preparation of claims narratives, quantification, and supporting evidence.</li><li>Monitor costs, risks, and opportunities and maintain commercial trackers.</li><li>Prepare meeting notes and follow-ups; maintain documentation quality.</li><li>Apply company contract management standards, templates, and controls.</li></ul><p><strong>Qualifications & Experience</strong></p><ul><li>2–3 years in contract administration, commercial support or handling of claims, and analysis of Terms and Conditions of Contract.</li><li>Bachelor’s degree in engineering or relevant discipline.</li><li>Experience in the energy sector (O&G, power generation, EPC/EPCM) is an added advantage.</li><li>Proficiency in English; able to draft contractual letters and interpret contract clauses.</li><li>Strong MS Office and SharePoint skills.</li></ul><p><strong>Core Competencies</strong></p><ul><li>Fast learner: able to grasp new concepts quickly and follow structured instructions.</li><li>Effective team player in diverse, cross-functional, multinational environments.</li><li>Analytical thinker able to interpret contractual language and connect facts to commercial outcomes.</li><li>Clear and concise written communication; professional email and documentation skills.</li><li>Strong organizational skills; maintains accurate records and trackers.</li></ul>",
